description: She's a girl. She's a space-pirate. She's Sardine - and she's back! With four Sardine books now published in the United States, our favorite red-headed space pirate has a growing number of young fans. Now appearing in her fifth collection of ten side-splitting space adventures is Sardine, her stories told in engaging, scribbly artwork by Emmanuel Guibert.
name: Vol. 5

deck: Find out what happens when BTTF producer Bob Gale and original Jennifer Parker actress, Melora Hardin, accidentally go into the past and help Eric Stoltz keep the role of Marty McFly.
description: After doing an interview with a website, producer Bob Gale feels bad over the original Jennifer Parker getting fired from the movie when Marty McFly was recast.

deck: After sitting in Bob Gale's electric car during a thunder and lightning storm, Bob and Melora Hardin believe they're still in the present but find they have journeyed back to the 80s when 'Back to the Future' was being filmed.
description: What will happen when Melora gives young Eric Stoltz a pep talk to try to help him keep the role of Marty McFly?

deck: THIS ISLAND IS UP TO NO GOOD...
description:
When Reese is forced to go on a boating trip with his family, the last thing he expects is to be shipwrecked on an island - especially one swarming with weird plants and animals. What starts out as a bad vacation turns into a frantic adventure, as the castaways must find a way to escape while dodging the island's lethal inhabitants. With few resources, and a mysterious entity on the hunt, each secret unlocked could save them ... or spell their doom.

One thing Reese knows for sure: THIS IS ONE BAD ISLAND.
name: GN
